ConstantAliasProxy, EventAliasProxy
public abstract class AliasProxy
extends IdentifiedElementProxy

An alias definition used to assign a simple name to a commonly used expression.

Aliases are used in to separate ways in modules.

  • To define named constants representing integers or ranges. Such aliases are of type ConstantAliasProxy and occur in the constant alias list of a module.
  • To give names to groups of events that are used in several different edges or graphs of a module. Such aliases are of type EventAliasProxy and occur in the event alias list of a module.

Each alias has a name and a value bound to the name. The name can be an arbitrary identifier. In particular, it can be indexed, as aliases can also be defined iteratively in a foreach construct (ForeachEventAliasProxy). The value is an arbitrary expression, its type can vary depending on the particular kind of alias.

Robi Malik
